Hello,
I've converted my JUnit test code  with your  convert-junit-assertions-to-assertj.sh script.
In most cases I have no problems and got a very good result. But at some tests I got into trouble (no compile any more ...) . As example here are some git diff's between JUnit code and now after the conversion.
Can you explain, what going wrong with that?


Here are two examples for successful conversion:
-    assertEquals("'ABcDe ='", StringHandling.addSingleQuotes("ABcDe ="));
+    assertThat(StringHandling.addSingleQuotes("ABcDe =")).isEqualTo("'ABcDe ='");

-    assertEquals("\"ABcDe =\"", StringHandling.addDoubleQuotes("ABcDe ="));
+    assertThat(StringHandling.addDoubleQuotes("ABcDe =")).isEqualTo("\"ABcDe =\"");

And here two example blocks which goes wrong:
-    assertEquals("12.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("12.34"));
-    assertEquals("34.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("34,34"));
-    assertEquals("1234.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1,234.34"));
-    assertEquals("1234.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1.234,34"));
-    assertEquals("1234567.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1,234,567.34"));
-    assertEquals("1234567.34", StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1.234.567,34"));
+    assertThat(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("0")).isEqualTo("0");
+    assertThat(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("12.34")).isEqualTo("12.34");
+    assertThat(34")).as("34.34").isEqualTo(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("34);
+    assertThat(234.34")).as("1234.34").isEqualTo(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1);
+    assertThat(34")).as("1234.34").isEqualTo(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1.234);
+    assertThat(234).as("1234567.34").isCloseTo(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1, within(567.34")));
+    assertThat(34")).as("1234567.34").isEqualTo(StringHandling.fixFPNumberFormat("1.234.567);

-    assertEquals("/home/linhrowe/Source/java/JCompPosition/examples/test_gencadpanel.cad", StringHandling.changeFileExtension("/home/linhrowe/Source/java/JCompPosition/examples/test_gencadpanel.pnl", "cad"));
+    assertThat(StringHandling.changeFileExtension("/home/linhrowe/Source/java/JCompPosition/examples/test_gencadpanel.pnl","cad").isEqualTo("/home/linhrowe/Source/java/JCompPosition/examples/test_gencadpanel.cad"));

If you need further informations, please contact me.

Bye
Roman
